21/11/2005
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- Interior Minister Rumen Petkov announced on Sunday (20 November) that the ministry is launching a campaign against customs fraud. He has ordered a detailed report on all suspected cases in which customs officers may have participated in smuggling. The report, expected within ten days, will be submitted to Prime Minister Sergey Stanishev and Finance Minister Plamen Oresharski. Petkov also plans to propose that law enforcement agencies be allowed access to customs databases. Access until now has been restricted. (bTV, Mediapool - 20/11/05)
